cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper is about crowd counting in video surveillance, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a domain adaptation method, which involves training a model on synthetic data and adapting it to real-world scenes, which falls under the scope of machine learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with density estimation, which is a subfield of computer vision, and involves analyzing and interpreting images to estimate the density of objects in a given area. Therefore, cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with video surveillance, which involves monitoring and analyzing video footage to detect and prevent crime, and falls under the scope of computer security. Hence, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is another possible sub-category.
